[src:martingale-theory/conditional-expectation] Note that unlike $\mu _{X}$ , the conditional expectation $e_{X}$ is not generally unique: there may be multiple minimizers of the mean squared error.
[src:martingale-theory/conditional-expectation] In the context of linear regression, this lack of uniqueness is called multicollinearity.
[src:martingale-theory/conditional-expectation] Conditional expectation is unique up to a set of measure zero in $\mathbb {R} ^{n}$ .
[src:martingale-theory/conditional-expectation] The measure used is the pushforward measure induced by Y.
